#. type: Title #
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Configuring routes"
msgid "Configuring Xdebug"
msgstr "配置路由"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Xdebug lets an IDE stop PHP code on breakpoints while the application handles a web request, console command, or test.  The IDE listens for debug connections. PHP starts the request and Xdebug connects back to the IDE."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Yii works with the regular Xdebug setup. Configure Xdebug for the PHP runtime that executes the code and make sure the IDE can map runtime paths to project files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Checkout"
msgid "Check Xdebug"
msgstr "结账"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Use Xdebug 3. The default debug port is `9003`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Without Docker, install Xdebug for the PHP executable that runs the application, then check it:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (shell)
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"php --version\n"
"php --ri xdebug\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "In `php.ini` or an Xdebug-specific ini file, enable step debugging:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (ini)
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"xdebug.mode=develop,debug\n"
"xdebug.start_with_request=trigger\n"
"xdebug.client_host=127.0.0.1\n"
"xdebug.client_port=9003\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "`trigger` starts a debug session only when a browser extension, query parameter, cookie, or `XDEBUG_SESSION` environment variable asks for it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "With Docker, the Yii application template installs Xdebug in the development image. Enable step debugging in `docker/dev/override.env`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (dotenv)
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"XDEBUG_MODE=develop,debug\n"
"XDEBUG_CONFIG=\"client_host=host.docker.internal idekey=phpstorm\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Keep the default `SERVER_NAME=:80` from `docker/dev/.env` unless the application needs a different Caddy address.  Set the browser port with `DEV_PORT` in `docker/.env`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (dotenv)
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "DEV_PORT=80\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "On Linux, Docker must resolve `host.docker.internal` to the host gateway. The current Yii application template already has this in `docker/compose.yml`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (yaml)
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"services:\n"
"  app:\n"
"    extra_hosts:\n"
"      - \"host.docker.internal:host-gateway\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Rebuild the development image if Xdebug was added after the image had already been built:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (shell)
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "make build\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "PhpStorm metadata"
msgid "PhpStorm"
msgstr "PhpStorm 元数据"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In **Settings** > **PHP** > **Debug**, check that Xdebug listens on port `9003`. Start listening with\n"
"**Run** > **Start Listening for PHP Debug Connections**.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For browser debugging, install a browser extension from **Settings** > **PHP** > **Debug**. In the extension options,\n"
"use `phpstorm` as the IDE key.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "When PHP runs in Docker, configure a server in **Settings** > **PHP** > **Servers**:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Name: `localhost`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Host: `localhost`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Port: `80`, or the host port configured by `DEV_PORT`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Debugger: `Xdebug`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Path mapping: map the project root on the host to `/app` in the container."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Use the project root for the mapping. Mapping only `public/` leaves files under `src/`, `config/`, and `vendor/` unmapped. The path in the container must match the path used by PHP. In the default template, the project is mounted into `/app`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "For local PHP, PhpStorm usually uses the same filesystem paths as PHP, so path mappings are usually unnecessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "VS Code"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Install the [PHP Debug](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=xdebug.php-debug) extension."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "For PHP that runs on the same filesystem as VS Code, create `.vscode/launch.json`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (json)
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"version\": \"0.2.0\",\n"
"  \"configurations\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"Listen for Xdebug\",\n"
"      \"type\": \"php\",\n"
"      \"request\": \"launch\",\n"
"      \"port\": 9003\n"
"    }\n"
"  ]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "For Docker, add path mappings:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (json)
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"version\": \"0.2.0\",\n"
"  \"configurations\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"Listen for Xdebug\",\n"
"      \"type\": \"php\",\n"
"      \"request\": \"launch\",\n"
"      \"port\": 9003,\n"
"      \"pathMappings\": {\n"
"        \"/app\": \"${workspaceFolder}\"\n"
"      }\n"
"    }\n"
"  ]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Start this configuration before running the web request, command, or test."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Zed"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Install or enable the PHP extension in Zed. It provides the `Xdebug` debug adapter."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Create `.zed/debug.json`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (json)
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[\n"
"  {\n"
"    \"label\": \"PHP: Listen to Xdebug\",\n"
"    \"adapter\": \"Xdebug\",\n"
"    \"request\": \"launch\",\n"
"    \"port\": 9003\n"
"  }\n"
"]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (json)
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[\n"
"  {\n"
"    \"label\": \"PHP: Listen to Xdebug\",\n"
"    \"adapter\": \"Xdebug\",\n"
"    \"request\": \"launch\",\n"
"    \"port\": 9003,\n"
"    \"pathMappings\": {\n"
"      \"/app\": \"$ZED_WORKTREE_ROOT\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/configuring-xdebug.md
msgid "Start the configuration with **debugger: start** before running the web request, command, or test. Zed can also load debug configurations from `.vscode/launch.json` when `.zed/debug.json` is absent."
msgstr ""

